TruthLens — Privacy Policy

Last Updated: November 20, 2025

TruthLens (“we,” “us,” or “our”) provides an AI-powered analysis tool that allows users to submit images, screenshots, and text for analysis. We take privacy seriously. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use the TruthLens mobile application (“App”).

Information We Collect 1.1. User-Provided Content
We collect the content you choose to submit, including:

Photos, screenshots, and images you upload for analysis

Text you provide as context

Category selections related to the analysis

This content is used only to generate results and maintain your analysis history within the App.

1.2. Usage Data

We automatically collect technical data such as:

Device model, OS version

App usage events (e.g., buttons tapped, screens viewed)

Crash logs, performance data

This helps us improve the App and fix bugs.

1.3. Subscription & Purchase Information

If you subscribe to TruthLens Pro, we may collect:

Purchase history

Subscription status

Transaction identifiers

All payments are processed by Apple. We do not store or have access to your full payment information.

How We Use Your Information
We use your data to:

Process AI analyses

Maintain your analysis history

Improve App performance and user experience

Provide customer support

Manage subscriptions and entitlements

Detect abuse, fraud, or misuse

Your content is never used to train AI models unless you explicitly consent (we do not request this by default).

How We Store & Protect Your Data
Images and text you submit are securely transmitted to our AI processing pipeline (OpenAI, Google, or similar).

Only the minimum necessary data is stored.

Images may be temporarily stored for the duration of the analysis process.

Analysis results and timestamps may be stored locally on your device and/or in our secure database.

Industry-standard encryption is used in transit and at rest.

We do not sell or rent your data. Ever.

Sharing Your Information
We may share limited data with:

AI processing providers (for generating results)

Analytics tools (anonymous usage insights only)

RevenueCat (subscription validation)

Apple (billing & fraud prevention)

We do not share your content with advertisers, data brokers, or any third parties unrelated to the App’s core functionality.

Your Choices & Rights
You can:

Delete images from your analysis history

Remove the App at any time

Request data deletion (email below)

Manage subscription status through your Apple ID settings

If required by your region, you may also request:

A copy of the data we hold

Correction of inaccurate information

Children’s Privacy
TruthLens is not intended for anyone under 16. We do not knowingly collect data from children under this age.

International Data Transfers
Our servers or AI providers may process data in locations outside your country. We rely on legal mechanisms (such as Standard Contractual Clauses) when applicable.

Changes to This Policy
We may update this policy from time to time. If we make significant changes, we will notify you in-app or via an updated effective date.

Contact Us
If you have questions or need to request data deletion:

TruthLens Support
YoGeeStudios@gmail.com
